==English==

===Etymology===
< Medieval Latin ''[[entitas]]'' < Latin, present participle of ''[[esse]]'', "to be".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|entity|entities}}
# [[Something]] or [[somebody]] that [[exist]]s as an [[individual]] [[unit]]. Often used for [[organisation]]s which have no physical form.
# {{computing}} An [[organized]] [[array]] or [[set]] of individual [[element]]s or [[part]]s.
# Being; existence.
#:''The group successfully maintains its tribal entity.''
#:The policy of the government of the United States is to seek . . . to preserve Chinese territorial and administrative ''entity'' 
::::::::::::::::::::::::::&nbsp;-- [[Wikipedia:George F. Kennan|G.F.Kennan]]

